Description: I have up for sale an LSL T-Bone Custom telecaster guitar. This beauty is named “Wichita”. It has a swamp ash body with a maple neck and fret board. The fret board radius is 7 ¼-in. The neck is C shaped and measures .84” at the 1st fret and .90” at the 12th fret. I had LSL sand the back of the neck and apply an oil finish. This makes the neck feel incredibly smooth. You won’t feel any stickiness here. No need to worry about fret wear. I had the frets upgraded to 6105 stainless steel. Besides being nearly impervious to wear they make bending a breeze. The weight is very light at 6lbs 11oz. The pickups are the original LSL pickups which came with the guitar. This guitar has a humbucker pickup in the neck position, which can be split by pulling up the tone control. The bridge pickup is a single coil. The guitar is in excellent condition and sounds incredible. When you strum a chord, you can feel the entire body resonate in your hands. The guitar has been lightly reliced by LSL. If you look closely at the pictures you will see where they have lightly checked the finish. I was told that this allows the guitar to breathe and opens up the sound. I do not have the original hard case but I will provide a very nice rigid gig bag. When I bought this guitar, I had to wait 6 months for the custom order. You can get it in a few days. Check out my feedbacks and buy with confidence.
Title: LSL T-Bone Custom with Upgrades
